        acceptedAnswer: {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          text: 'For a standard straight grid layout in a rectangular room, add 10% extra tile for waste. Diagonal installations require 15% extra, and herringbone or complex patterns need 15-20% additional material. Rooms with many cuts around cabinets, pipes, and fixtures can push waste even higher. Always buy all tile at once from the same production lot, since colors and calibration can vary between lots.',
        },
