          text: 'First, calculate your room area in square feet by multiplying the length by the width. Next, calculate the area of one tile in square feet by multiplying the tile length by the tile width (convert inches to feet first by dividing by 12). Divide the room area by the tile area to get the base number of tiles, then multiply by your waste factor (1.10 for 10% waste). Round up to the nearest whole number. Finally, divide by the number of tiles per box to determine how many boxes to order.',
